ExecDesc: PHP Arbitrary File Location Upload Vulnerability

ExecDesc: TCP NOOP Packet Variant HP-UNIX
EngDesc: This threat sends a TCP packet that appears to be part of an existing valid connection with a NOOP sled in it. A NOOP sled is used by shellcode to insure that the injected code will execute. Unfortunately, there are many other reasons why a NOOP might appear in traffic. This threat utilized equivalent assembly instructions to the standard NOOP instruction.

ExecDesc: UDP NOOP Variant HP-UNIX
EngDesc: This threat sends UDP packets with a payload filled with NOOP assembly instructions. This gets flagged on IDS systems as a possible shellcode injection attack. NOOPs are used as a sled to insure more probability for shellcode to execute. Unfortunately, NOOPs are also quite common in binary downloads from websites as well, causing many false positives.

ExecDesc: PineApp Mail-SeCure confpremenu.php Export Log Command Injection
EngDesc:
A command execution vulnerability exists in PineApp Mail-SeCure. The vulnerability is due to an input validation
error in the confpremenu.php script while exporting logs.
A remote attacker can exploit this vulnerability by sending a specially crafted request to the vulnerable server.
Successful exploitation could result in commands being executed with root privileges.

ExecDesc: ESF pfSense webConfigurator firewall_aliases_edit.php Input Validation Error(IPv6 Version)
EngDesc: An input validation error vulnerability exists in Electric Sheep Fencing pfSense firewall. The vulnerability is due to insufficient validation of user supplied input when processing the addressN parameter in firewall_aliases_edit.php. A remote authenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability by sending a malicious request using the vulnerable parameter to the firewall. Successful exploitation could lead to remote code execution under the security context of the root user.

ExecDesc: PHP CDF File Handling Infinite Loop
EngDesc: A denial of service vulnerability has been reported in PHP. It is due to an error in the FileInfo module while handling nelements in the processing of CDF files. A successful attack will result in an infinite loop, which can cause a denial of service condition.

ExecDesc: PHP unserialize Call SPL ArrayObject and SPLObjectStorage Memory Corruption
EngDesc: A memory corruption vulnerability exists in PHP. The vulnerability is due to type confusion in the unserialize() function for SPL ArrayObject and SPLObjectStorage. An unsuccessful attack will result in a denial of service condition.
